# Phase 2: Design System & Component Library

## Objective

Build the complete visual foundation for ProjectSeaT before developing any application screens. The goal of this phase is to create a reusable design system and component library that will be used consistently throughout the project.

Do **not** create any feature-specific pages, dashboards, or workflows in this phase. Focus only on the design language and reusable UI components.

---

# 1. Establish the Visual Identity

Create a clean, modern interface inspired by the maritime world. The design should feel professional, elegant, and timeless without relying on cliché nautical graphics such as anchors, ropes, ship wheels, waves, or pirate elements.

The visual inspiration should come from:

* Sea voyagers' uniforms
* Modern ships
* Harbors
* Maritime architecture
* Coastal sunsets
* Ocean horizons

The overall aesthetic should be minimal, spacious, and premium.

---

# 2. Official Color Theme

Use the following color palette throughout the project.

| Role       | Name        | Hex     |
| ---------- | ----------- | ------- |
| Primary    | Harbor Navy | #12355B |
| Secondary  | Ocean Blue  | #2F6690 |
| Accent     | Sunset Gold | #F4A261 |
| Highlight  | Coral       | #E76F51 |
| Background | Pearl       | #FAF7F2 |

Color usage guidelines:

* Harbor Navy should be the primary brand color.
* Ocean Blue should be used for interactive elements.
* Sunset Gold should be reserved for primary CTAs, progress indicators, achievements, and important actions.
* Coral should be used sparingly for emphasis and notifications.
* Pearl should be the primary application background.

---

# 3. Typography

Use **Manrope** as the primary typeface.

Create a complete typography system including:

* Display
* H1
* H2
* H3
* H4
* Body Large
* Body
* Small
* Caption

Define:

* Font weights
* Line heights
* Letter spacing
* Responsive scaling

---

# 4. Spacing System

Create an 8-point spacing system.

Spacing scale:

4px

8px

12px

16px

24px

32px

48px

64px

80px

96px

Apply this consistently across every component.

---

# 5. Border Radius

Define standard radii:

Buttons: 12px

Inputs: 12px

Cards: 16px

Dialogs: 20px

Pills: Fully rounded

---

# 6. Elevation

Create four elevation levels:

* None
* Small
* Medium
* Large

Use soft shadows.

Avoid excessive blur or floating effects.

---

# 7. Design Tokens

Create reusable design tokens for:

* Colors
* Typography
* Spacing
* Radius
* Borders
* Shadows
* Animation duration
* Opacity
* Z-index

These should be centralized for future scalability.

---

# 8. Layout Components

Develop reusable layout components.

Include:

## App Layout

* Header
* Main Content Area
* Optional Footer

## Header

Include placeholders for:

* ProjectSeaT logo
* Navigation
* User profile
* Notifications
* Settings

## Main Container

Responsive page wrapper.

## Section Container

Reusable section component containing:

* Title
* Subtitle
* Content
* Optional actions

---

# 9. UI Component Library

Create reusable UI components.

## Buttons

Variants:

* Primary
* Secondary
* Outline
* Ghost
* Icon
* Loading
* Disabled

---

## Cards

Variants:

* Standard
* Elevated
* Interactive
* Compact

---

## Form Components

Create:

* Text Input
* Search Field
* Password Input
* Textarea
* Dropdown
* Checkbox
* Radio Button
* Toggle Switch

---

## Navigation Components

Create:

* Navbar
* Sidebar
* Breadcrumb
* Tabs

---

## Feedback Components

Create:

* Alert
* Badge
* Status Chip
* Toast
* Tooltip
* Modal
* Progress Bar

---

## Data Components

Create:

* Table
* Timeline
* Accordion
* Empty State
* Pagination
* Skeleton Loader

---

# 10. Icons

Use **Lucide Icons** only.

Maintain:

* Consistent stroke width
* Rounded appearance
* Uniform sizing

---

# 11. Motion

Do not use Framer Motion or any paid libraries.

Implement animations using:

* CSS transitions
* Native browser animations

Include:

* Fade
* Slide
* Scale
* Hover
* Button press
* Loading transitions

Animations should be subtle and fast (200-300ms).

---

# 12. Responsive Design

Design for:

* Desktop
* Tablet
* Mobile

Ensure all components adapt cleanly across breakpoints.

---

# 13. Accessibility

Ensure every component supports:

* Keyboard navigation
* Focus indicators
* Proper contrast ratios
* Semantic HTML
* ARIA attributes where appropriate

---

# 14. Technology Stack

Use:

* React
* TypeScript
* Tailwind CSS
* Lucide Icons
* CSS transitions

Do not introduce additional UI libraries unless absolutely necessary.

---

# Deliverables

At the end of Phase 2, the project should include:

* Complete Harbor Sunset design system
* Centralized design tokens
* Typography system
* Color system
* Spacing system
* Elevation system
* Responsive layout components
* Reusable UI component library
* Navigation components
* Form components
* Feedback components
* Data display components
* Accessibility-ready components
* Motion guidelines

No feature-specific pages or business logic should be developed during this phase. The outcome should be a polished, reusable design foundation that all future phases will build upon.
